00:00:03.639 --> 00:00:06.180
How to Make New England Clam Chowder.

00:00:06.180 --> 00:00:10.880
There are almost as many variations of this
hearty soup as there are varieties of clams.

00:00:10.880 --> 00:00:14.139
Try this basic recipe for a satisfying, warming
meal.

00:00:14.139 --> 00:00:23.210
You will need 5 lb. hard-shelled clams 4 oz.
salt pork or pancetta 1 yellow onion 1 celery

00:00:23.210 --> 00:00:34.820
stalk 3 potatoes 1 c. milk 1 bay leaf 2 sprigs
fresh thyme 1 c. heavy cream Salt Pepper Parsley

00:00:34.820 --> 00:00:56.679
Oyster crackers A large soup pot A measuring
cup A paring knife 

00:00:56.679 --> 00:01:01.710
and 2 tbsp. flour.

00:01:01.710 --> 00:01:02.730
Step 1.

00:01:02.730 --> 00:01:04.370
Discard any clams that did not open.

00:01:04.370 --> 00:01:09.540
Let the clams cool; then cut the meat out
with a paring knife and chop coarsely.

00:01:09.540 --> 00:01:19.299
Wash the soup pot.

00:01:19.299 --> 00:01:20.299
Step 2.

00:01:20.299 --> 00:01:23.729
Dice the salt pork or pancetta and add to
the soup pot.

00:01:23.729 --> 00:01:25.130
Cook until crisp.

00:01:25.130 --> 00:01:26.140
Step 3.

00:01:26.140 --> 00:01:30.090
Dice the onion and celery and add to the salt
pork or pancetta.

00:01:30.090 --> 00:01:31.149
Cook until soft.

00:01:31.149 --> 00:01:35.619
For a quicker recipe, substitute two cups
freshly shucked clams or three cans minced

00:01:35.619 --> 00:01:38.369
clams, plus one bottle clam juice.

00:01:38.369 --> 00:01:39.590
Step 4.

00:01:39.590 --> 00:01:43.680
Stir in the reserved clam broth or bottled
clam juice, plus the milk.

00:01:43.680 --> 00:01:46.240
Peel the potatoes and cut into cubes.

00:01:46.240 --> 00:01:49.090
Add them to the pot with the bay leaf and
thyme and simmer until tender.

00:01:49.090 --> 00:01:50.090
Step 5.

00:01:50.090 --> 00:01:51.090
Wash the clams thoroughly under cold running
water and add them to three cups boiling water

00:01:51.090 --> 00:01:52.090
in a large soup pot.

00:01:52.090 --> 00:01:53.090
Boil for three to five minutes.

00:01:53.090 --> 00:01:54.090
Mix two tablespoons flour with two tablespoons
cold water; and cook and stir for one minute

00:01:54.090 --> 00:01:55.090
for thicker chowder.

00:01:55.090 --> 00:01:56.090
Step 6.

00:01:56.090 --> 00:01:57.090
Add the cream and the clam meat.

00:01:57.090 --> 00:01:58.090
Simmer and season with salt and pepper.

00:01:58.090 --> 00:01:59.090
Sprinkle with parsley and serve with oyster
crackers.

00:01:59.090 --> 00:02:00.340
You'll be saying "chowdah" before you know
it.

00:02:00.340 --> 00:02:01.340
Step 7.

00:02:01.340 --> 00:02:02.340
Remove the steamed clams and set aside.

